title: For Sale:  ISRAELI DEFENSE FORCES M-21/M1A. ISRAELI SNIPER RIFLE
postcontent:
FOR SALE:
ISRAELI DEFENSE FORCES (IDF) M21/M1A 7.62MM SNIPER RIFLE PACKAGE

Sniper rifle system used by IDF snipers, from the mid-1980s to late 1990s. Around the year 2000, Springfield Armory brought approximately 600 M-21 kits (minus the M14 F/A receivers) into the US. After the kits were sold, Springfield Armory unloaded all extra parts at Camp Perry.

This rifle is built on a Springfield Armory receiver, assembled with new or with-in specification USGI parts, the only Non GI part is the receiver. All IDF parts were purchased at Camp Perry.

Barrel type:  New TRW bolt, SACO-LOWELL-MAREMOUNT chrome-lined 1-12 twist, 4 groove barrel. The barrel is dated 2-69. 

Barrel specs are: Throat- .5, Muzzle- 0, Headspace-1.630, USGI flash suppressor was reamed to National Match M14 spec. The gas cylinder was unitized to the front stock ferrule via TIG welding per National Match specs. 

The scope is a genuine IDF Nimrod scope with 6x40 range finding reticle. The scope also has an M118 (7.62Nato) elevation knob. The scope is mounted to the receiver by a genuine IDF steel scope mount.

The stock is an IDF modified GI fiberglass stock. Cheek peace/riser, 1st gen Harris Bi-pod, bi-pod mount, sling swivels, and butt-pad are all IDF parts.

This weapons package is not for your average M1A enthusiast. It has an accurized chamber, all ammo used should be 1988 to present day SAAMI minimal spec ammo, such as Lakecity/US M80 ball (shoots great), M118, Federal, .308win quality ammo. 

Extra accessories are a genuine IDF case, two magazines ( 1 in wrapper), one piece cleaning rod, and M1A tools.

[ NO TRADES, CASH TALKS. PREFER FACE TO FACE ]

title: For Sale:  Galil Original Magnum Research Model 372
postcontent: Up for your consideration is a very nice Galil It is an early Magnum Research import. It is not an Action Arms. The difference between the 2 are very important to value. Far less of the Magnum Research were imported About 100-1 (Research on the Internet) The Magnum Research has an Original Galil flash hider and bayonet lug. It will accept bayonets from an M-16 or M-15 The Action Arms imports are transitional guns.
